external_knowledge:
- IMDb rating is a measure of a movie's quality based on user reviews, ranging from 1 (lowest) to 10 (highest); 
- Total box office represents the cumulative earnings of a movie in millions of dollars;
- The most common genre is the genre with the highest number of movies produced by a studio;
- The director with the most movies is the director who has produced the highest number of movies within a studio.
